    <text id="F3502T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Dr. Joseph Hills Clintock certifies that John Ault remains unfit for duty for at
                    least another thirty days.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Adjutant Gen. Thomas USA</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-03-04">March 4, 1863</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>Chaplain John Ault of the 126th Regt Penn. Vols. having applied and received
                    leave of absence from Maj. Genl. Joseph Hooker, I do hereby certify that I have
                    examined this officer, and find that he is recovering, but is, as yet closely
                    confined to his bed and absolutely unable to travel to rejoin his regiment. He
                    has been absent since the 17th of January 1863, and will not be able to return
                    in less than thirty days from this date. dated at London, Franklin Co., Penna.
                    this 4th day of March 1863.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed><abbr expan="Joseph">Jos.</abbr> Hills McClintock<lb/> Attending
                        Physician</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">A. B. See former certificate for description of his
                        disease.<lb/><lb/> I hereby certify that Joseph H. McClintock, the signer of
                        the above certificate, is, what he represents himself to be, a regular
                        Practising Physician, and the attending Physician of Chaplain John Ault.<lb/><lb/>
                        <abbr expan="Joseph">Jos.</abbr> Crawford</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
